00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:04,000
The World Health Organization, WHO for short,

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,820
is the authority for health within the United Nations

3
00:00:06,820 --> 00:00:08,000
system.

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,330
It is responsible for providing leadership on global health

5
00:00:11,330 --> 00:00:14,460
matters, shaping the health research agenda,

6
00:00:14,460 --> 00:00:16,960
setting norms and standards, articulating

7
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:20,540
evidence-based policy options, providing technical support

8
00:00:20,540 --> 00:00:25,710
to countries, and monitoring and assessing health trends.

9
00:00:25,710 --> 00:00:29,820
WHO communicates information about global health in order

10
00:00:29,820 --> 00:00:34,430
to inform citizens, donors, policymakers, and organizations

11
00:00:34,430 --> 00:00:35,850
around the world.

12
00:00:35,850 --> 00:00:39,150
Their primary publication is World Health Report.

13
00:00:39,150 --> 00:00:43,190
Each issue focuses on a specific aspect of global health,

14
00:00:43,190 --> 00:00:47,770
and includes statistics and experts' assessments.

15
00:00:47,770 --> 00:00:51,660
WHO also maintains an open, online repository

16
00:00:51,660 --> 00:00:54,010
of global health data.

17
00:00:54,010 --> 00:00:56,810
WHO provides some data visualizations,

18
00:00:56,810 --> 00:00:58,620
which helps them communicate more

19
00:00:58,620 --> 00:01:00,310
effectively with the public.

20
00:01:00,310 --> 00:01:04,690
As an example, the graph shows the World Energy Consumption

21
00:01:04,690 --> 00:01:08,120
during 2001 to 2003.

